<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRADING PLACES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN KING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here's the lineup for Showtime's "Directed By" series, week by week: 
</P>
<P>
 "Texan" 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday at 10 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Directed by Treat Williams. Starring Dabney Coleman, Dana Delany, Charles 
Durning and Brian Doyle Murray, with a cameo by Williams. David Mamet penned 
this mystery about an ex-fighter pilot who suspects his beautiful young wife of 
shady dealings after he learns she's withdrawn a huge sum of money from her 
bank account. 
</P>
<P>
 "On Hope" 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday at 10:30 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Directed by JoBeth Williams. Starring Annette O'Toole and Mercedes Ruehl, with 
a cameo by Williams. Lynn Mamet, David's sister, wrote this poignant drama, 
based on her short story, about a friendship between two distinctively 
different women. 
</P>
<P>
 "Leslie's Folly" 
</P>
<P>
 Oct. 9 at 10 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Directed by Kathleen Turner. Starring Anne Archer, Charles Durning, Mary Kay 
Place, John Shea, with a cameo by Turner. Lynn Mamet also wrote this script, 
based on her short story, about a woman with three children who must cope with 
an unplanned pregnancy. 
</P>
<P>
 "Override" 
</P>
<P>
 Oct. 16 at 10 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Directed by Danny Glover. Starring Erika Alexander, Emily Lloyd and Lou 
Diamond Philips. Dianne Houston penned the script of this futuristic drama 
about an unwed mother of two who drives a robot-controlled tractor-trailer 
truck. Her life changes dramatically when she meets a handsome fellow driver. 
</P>
<P>
 "Partners" 
</P>
<P>
 Oct. 23 at 10 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Directed by Peter Weller. Starring Graham Beckel, Griffin Dunne, Marg 
Helgenberger, Joseph Maher, with a cameo by Weller. Weller and Ebbe Roe Smith 
penned the adaptation of Tom McGuane's short story about a rising younger 
lawyer whose career is placed in jeopardy when he meets a former lover. 
Nominated for the 1993 Academy Award for best short subject. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Gift" 
</P>
<P>
 Oct. 30 at 10 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Directed by Laura Dern. Starring Bonnie Bedelia, Peter Horton, Diane Ladd, 
Mary Kay Place, Isabella Rossellini and Mary Steenburgen. Emily Tracy scripted 
this drama, based on an original story by Tracy and Dern, which focuses on one 
day in the life of a woman suffering from the breakup of a relationship with 
her boyfriend. SUSAN KING 
</P>
