<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARBON MONOXIDE DETECTORS MANDATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chicago becomes the first major U.S. city to require carbon monoxide detectors 
in homes and buildings ranging from theaters to museums. 
</P>
<P>
 The new law, effective Saturday, triggered a run on the devices, which retail 
between $30 and $50. 
</P>
