<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PUC GIVETH AND THE PUC TAKETH AWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 My recent monthly telephone bill showed two credits allowed by the Public 
Utilities Commission in the total amount of $1.03.While I was consulting a 
financial expert about how to invest this windfall, "The Bottom Line" (Sept. 
16) reported rate increases -- allowed by the same PUC -- of $2.90 and $6.05, 
respectively, per month. 
</P>
<P>
 I am at a loss as to how the PUC can act in this manner. I believe that only a 
second Sigmund Freud could straighten out this ridiculous PUC policy. 
</P>
<P>
 RUDOLF STEINER 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
