<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: SERVICE: GROUPS GET CITY GRANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three Westside community service groups have received city grants to continue 
their work. 
</P>
<P>
 Recipients were: 
</P>
<P>
 * The West Los Angeles-based Self-Help and Recovery Exchange program, known as 
SHARE, operated by the Emotional Health Assn., which received $200 for its free 
emotional and mental health help programs. 
</P>
<P>
 * Pets are Wonderful Support (P.A.W.S./LA), an HIV-care nonprofit agency based 
in West Hollywood, but serving many people in western Los Angeles, received 
$100. 
</P>
<P>
 * The city attorney office's Dispute Resolution Program, created to mediate 
problems in Venice's Oakwood community, was given $125. 
</P>
<P>
 The grants are funded through the city's general purpose fund. 
</P>
