<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOMEOWNER'S EXEMPTION SERVICE IS OFFERED FREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Responding to numerous calls about mail solicitations, Los Angeles County 
Assessor Kenneth P. Hahn cautions homeowners against paying a fee to 
organizations for filing homeowner exemption forms. 
</P>
<P>
 "The county assessor's office provides this service free of charge," Hahn 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Under California law, property owners are entitled to an annual $7,000 
reduction in the taxable value of their principal residence," he said. "To 
receive the exemption, a homeowner must complete a proper exemption claim form, 
which the assessor's office automatically sends to all new homeowners soon 
after their purchase." 
</P>
<P>
 The forms are also available at any of the assessor' regional offices. 
</P>
<P>
 Property owners can check their tax bills to determine whether or not they are 
currently receiving a homeowner's exemption. 
</P>
</TEXT>
