<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANAL CORRECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I, too, have made the passage through the Panama Canal and I enjoyed the 
article ("Rite of Passage, Sept. 18), but I would like to correct a statement 
(in the accompanying illustration) that water is pumped into the lock.The 
marvel of the canal is that there are no pumps; it is operated on gravity flow 
through valves that are opened to allow the stored water from the man-made lake 
to fill the locks from openings in the bottom of the locks and continue on its 
way to the ocean. 
</P>
<P>
 BOB HENDRICKS 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego 
</P>
<P>
 Editor's note: Mr. Hendricks is correct. Our use of the word "pumped" was in 
error .  
</P>
