<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALI CAFE SORELY MISSED IN CANYON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sunday (Sept. 18) was a sad day for all of us in Silverado Canyon. The Pali 
Cafe closed. The Pali Cafe was one of the reasons we moved up here four years 
ago.It was a weekend treat for us to drive up to Silverado Canyon from Orange 
and enjoy a leisurely breakfast at the Pali. We enjoyed coming to a place where 
everyone was so friendly. 
</P>
<P>
 About 1989, we decided that if others could live up here so could we. Since 
that time, we've enjoyed two lifestyles -- the hustle and bustle of city life 
during the day, but evenings and weekends are spent at a more leisurely and 
relaxing pace. 
</P>
<P>
 In the past four years, we have made many friends at the Pali Cafe. There's 
still a real camaraderie in Silverado Canyon, but a piece is missing without 
the Pali. 
</P>
<P>
 ROSEMARY KRABBE 
</P>
<P>
 Silverado 
</P>
