. Shawn Gray threw two fourth-quarter touchdown passes to lead Texas El Paso 
(2-3, 1-2) to a 34-28 WAC victory over turnover-prone Hawaii (2-3, 0-3) at El 
Paso, Tex. Gray completed only six of 20 passes but threw for 174 yards and he 
