<HEADLINE>
<P>
HORSE RACING ROUNDUP; SUPER DERBY VICTORY SONG BY BACHARACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southland-based Soul Of The Matter, in his last race before the Breeder's Cup 
Classic in November, defeated co-favorite Concern by a neck to win the $750,000 
Super Derby at Louisiana Downs on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Soul Of The Matter, owned by composer Bert Bacharach and ridden by Kent 
Desormeaux, covered the 1 1/4 miles in 2:03 2/5 against a field reduced to six 
3-year-olds when two entrants were late scratches. 
</P>
<P>
 Soul Of The Matter, fifth in the Kentucky Derby, earned $450,000 for his 
fourth victory in seven starts this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Soul Of The Matter, trained by Dick Mandella, returned $5.80, $3.60 and $2.60. 
Concern, the Arkansas Derby winner ridden by Jerry Bailey, paid $3.20 and 
$2.40, while Bay Star, with Pat Day aboard, returned $3.00. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Blues Traveller edged Fastness by a length to win the $200,000 Bay Meadows 
Handicap for 3-year-olds. Blues Traveller, ridden by Gary Stevens, covered 1 
1/8 miles on turf in 1:46 and paid $6.20, $2.80, 2.40. Fastness returned $2.60 
and $2.40 and Wharf paid $3.20. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Taking Risks, the odds-on favorite, scored a 7 1/4-length victory in the 
$150,000 Maryland Million Classic at Laurel Race Course. 
</P>
