<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; EDWARDS, MITCHELL LEAD UCI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Popi Edwards had 15 kills and Stacy Mitchell added nine as UC Irvine beat Cal 
State Fullerton, 15-5, 15-4, 15-7, in a Big West Conference volleyball match 
Saturday night at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Jennifer Lipski had 10 kills and Chelsea Wilhite added seven for Fullerton, 
which fell to 0-15, 0-5 in conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Meredith Fletcher had 33 assists for the Anteaters (3-10, 2-4). Melissa 
Blackler led the Titans in assists with 24. 
</P>
<P>
 Mitchell had 14 digs and Edwards had 13. Blackler had 13 digs for Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Biola 3, Southern California College 0 -- Genevie Wright had 26 kills and 
Celeste Young added 19 for SCC (13-4, 3-2), which lost, 18-16, 15-11, 17-15. 
Biola is 11-6, 5-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Westmont 3, Concordia 0 -- Elaini Kollias had seven kills for Concordia (10-8, 
1-5), which lost, 15-12, 15-9, 15-9. Westmont is 2-4 in conference. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 3, Cal State Dominguez Hills 0 -- Shawna Parkinson had 15 kills for 
host Chapman (15-3), which won, 16-14, 15-11, 15-13. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 4, Concordia 0 -- Chris Chaparro scored two goals 
and Kevin Villar, Bryan Shoup, Matthew Clement and Jason Allen added one each 
for host SCC, which scored four first-half goals. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 6, Whittier 0 -- Cindy LeClair scored two goals for visiting Chapman 
(5-3). Teri Perkins, Amy Feniello, Carey Wright and Kathy Mulherin also scored. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 5, The Master's 0 -- Megan Conner and Joy 
Pelletier got two goals each for host SCC (4-5-1), which scored four goals in 
the second half. Deann Salcido scored SCC's other goal. 
</P>
<P>
 At the Stanford Invitational cross-country meet: 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton's Killeen 10th -- Heather Killeen finished 10th in 18:10 for Cal 
State Fullerton, which was 11th. UC Irvine's Laura Monson was 20th in 18:33. 
Irvine finished ninth. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA's Karen Hecox won the race in 17:14. The Bruins' Shelley Taylor, formerly 
of Edison High and Arkansas, was fourth in 17:40. Stanford won the meet. 
</P>
<P>
 At the NorCal water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine 9, Chaminade 2; USC 12, UCI 8 -- Peter Muller scored three goals and 
Omar Amr added two against Chaminade at Stanford. Tom Davis had seven saves, 
including a penalty shot. 
</P>
<P>
 Against USC, ranked second, Hrvoje Cizmic scored five goals to lead UCI. Craig 
Watson tied the score, 7-7, with four seconds left in the third quarter, but 
USC scored the next four goals to pull away. 
</P>
