<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUNTAIN VALLEY TENNIS TEAM MAKES FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fountain Valley's Los Caballeros tennis team defeated the Pacific Northwest, 
2-1, Saturday to advance to the finals of the USTA team nationals in Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 In doubles, Mitch Bridge and Dexter MacBride defeated Ned Hastings and Rob 
Peterson, 6-2, 6-0, and Steven Jung and Gerardo Rivera defeated Len Spencer and 
Kevin Jettgueyer, 6-2, 6-0.In singles, Los Caballeros' Doug Eisenman defaulted 
to Mark Wagner because of a back strain after splitting the first two sets. 
</P>
<P>
 A women's team from Orange County also advanced to the finals. The team, led 
by Sheri Norris, beat Texas, 2-1. Cammy McGregor beat Amy Webster, 6-3, 6-1, in 
singles. Linda Howell and Lisa Seeman defeated Julie Cast and Karen Koen, 6-4, 
6-1. The No. 2 doubles team of Norris and Betty Ann Dent lost to Cindy Crawford 
and Nancy Webster, 7-6, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Caballeros will play in the round-robin finals today against Northern 
California and Texas. 
</P>
