<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 'MISSING' SISTERS BACK HOME AFTER NIGHT ON TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two sisters who were reported missing Friday after disappearing from their 
South-Central Los Angeles junior high school returned home Saturday after 
spending the night on the town, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cristina and Elizabeth Gonzalez, 11 and 12, became the subjects of a 
round-the-clock search after their mother told police they failed to come home 
from school Friday afternoon. The girls told police they ditched school and 
rode the bus to Hollywood. They made their way home about 3 p.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think they had a good time," said Lt. James Voge, commanding officer of the 
Newton police station. "But I think they are regretting that now." 
</P>
