<HEADLINE>
<P>
THOUSAND OAKS SETTLES FOR SECOND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior Keith O'Doherty and junior Kim Mortensen each placed fourth in their 
respective races Saturday to lead the Thousand Oaks High boys' and girls' 
cross-country teams to second-place finishes in the Southwestern University 
Invitational in Georgetown, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Doherty timed 16 minutes over the three-mile course as Thousand Oaks, the 
No. 2-ranked team in the country by the Harrier magazine, totaled 44 
points.Top-ranked Kingwood, Tex., placed first with 37 points, paced by the 1-3 
finish of senior twins Brad and Brent Hauser. 
</P>
<P>
 Todd Disney (eighth in 16:48), Kevin Marsden (ninth in 16:52), Jeff Fischer 
(10th in 16:53) and Josh Carolan (13th in 17:08) rounded out Thousand Oaks' top 
five runners. 
</P>
<P>
 Marsden and Fischer were racing for only the second time this season after 
missing the first two meets with injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Mortensen ran 12:07 over the two-mile girls' course as Thousand Oaks totaled 
74 points. Kingwood placed five runners among the top 19 finishers for a 
46-point winning total. 
</P>
<P>
 Tara Marsden (15th in 12:49) and Bridgit Roy (16th in 12:49) were Thousand 
Oaks' No. 2 and No. 3 runners. 
</P>
