</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pierce College had hoped to air out its frustrations against Compton on 
Saturday afternoon. Instead, the Brahmas ended up adding to them. 
</P>
<P>
 Five second-half turnovers by Pierce enabled Compton to rally for a 24-16 
Western State Conference victory at Compton College. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite an erratic offense, Pierce held a 13-0 lead in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 That cushion quickly disappeared when Compton (3-0 overall, 2-0 in conference 
play) converted three turnovers into a 17-13 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Deon Hampton returned Josh Patterson's fumble six yards for Compton's first 
score. 
</P>
<P>
 Pierce quarterback David Muir (15 of 27, 147 yards, one touchdown) followed by 
throwing interceptions on the Brahmas' next three possessions as the Tartars 
added another 10 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Pierce Coach Bill Norton played Ash McNally at quarterback in the fourth 
quarter. McNally responded by leading Pierce to a first and goal at the Compton 
six. 
</P>
<P>
 However, the drive stalled and Pierce (0-3, 0-2) had to settle for a 27-yard 
Russell Gordon field goal and a 17-16 deficit.  
</P>
<P>
 Pierce held Compton on its next series. But McNally threw Pierce's fourth 
interception of the day to end the drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Compton responded with a five-minute, 70-yard drive that resulted in a 
three-yard touchdown run by Jachon Ramseur. 
