<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOSCOW TO INVESTIGATE STUDENT'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Prosecutors are opening an investigation into the death of an American 
exchange student who was found strangled outside his Moscow dormitory. 
</P>
<P>
 Anthony Riccio, 21, of Glastonbury, Conn., was apparently thrown off a 
16th-floor balcony Sept. 20 after being killed.Russian police at first 
suggested he had committed suicide. 
</P>
<P>
 The preliminary autopsy said Riccio had been murdered. The U.S. Embassy said 
"laboratory tests showed no drugs or alcohol in Mr. Riccio's blood." 
</P>
<P>
 The Brown University junior arrived in Moscow last month to study for a year 
at Russian State University for the Humanities in the American Collegiate 
Consortium program sponsored by Middlebury College in Vermont. 
</P>
<P>
 Five other Americans in Riccio's program were moved out of the dormitory and 
will continue their studies outside Moscow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
