<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOTER REGISTRATION ENDS OCT. 11 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The deadline for registering to vote in the Nov. 8 general election is Oct. 
11.To be eligible to vote, individuals must be U.S. citizens and at least 18 
years of age by Election Day. Those wishing to register can do so in person at 
the headquarters of the Registrar-Recorder/County Clerk at 12400 Imperial 
Highway in Norwalk. They can also request registration-by-mail forms at various 
locations, including county buildings, city halls, post offices and libraries, 
or by telephoning the county's election information system at (310) 462-2748. 
The information system is open 24 hours a day, seven days a week. The 
postage-paid forms are mailed within a day after the request is received. 
</P>
