<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTORCYCLIST KILLED IN PILEUP IN OXNARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A motorcyclist was killed early Saturday evening in a pileup on the Pacific 
Coast Highway at Pleasant Valley Road in Oxnard, a California Highway Patrol 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident at about 7:15 closed PCH in both directions from Pleasant Valley 
Road to Hueneme Road for several hours, forcing the CHP to route traffic 
through city streets. 
</P>
<P>
 Three other people were injured in the accident, when the black BMW they were 
riding in rolled over several times, the spokesman said. Two of the passengers 
were trapped in the vehicle for nearly half an hour, and rescue personnel had 
to cut them free of the wreckage. One person in the car was unhurt. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims were taken to St. Johns Regional Medical Center in Oxnard. One was 
treated and released. The other two were still being treated by doctors as of 
late Saturday, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The names of the victims and details of the crash were unavailable late 
Saturday, the CHP spokesman said. SCOTT HADLY 
