<P>
 Palme d'Or -- A Sept. 11 article about director Quentin Tarantino incorrectly 
reported the number of American films that have won the Palme d'Or at the 
Cannes Film Festival. As reader Steve Barr points out, 13 American films have 
won or shared the honor: "Marty" (1955), "Friendly Persuasion" (1957), "MASH" 
(1970), "Scarecrow" (1973), "The Conversation" (1974), "Taxi Driver" (1976), 
"All That Jazz" (1980), "Missing" (1982), "Paris, Texas" (1984), "sex, lies and 
videotape" (1989), "Wild at Heart" (1990), "Barton Fink" (1991) and Tarantino's 
"Pulp Fiction" this year. 
