 Some of the mutual fund industry's major growth-stock funds produced 
relatively low returns in 1992 and '93 and so far this year are in negative 
territory or up only slightly. But at most of these funds, assets haven't 
declined much, indicating that most shareholders have stayed put. 
</P>
